The Executive Secretary of the Plateau State Christian Pilgrims Welfare Board, Rev.  Fr George Gorap, has tasked  the Plateau pilgrims currently in the Holy Land to support the government for making it possible for them to undertake the spiritual journey to Israel Gorap who made the call at Galilee, Israel. enjoined them to pray for themselves and for the success of the Governor Simon Lalong’s led administration. He commended governor Lalong for advancing the cause of Christian pilgrimage in Plateau and in Nigeria as a whole. Rev. Fr Gorap urged the governor to remain focus in his developmental strides. He called on the well-meaning Christians in the state to complement the efforts of the state government by sponsoring Christians ‘ who are spiritually rich, but materially poor on Holy pilgrimage to Israel. ALSO READ: No panic over Finance Bill ― Finance minister The clergy also commended the Plateau pilgrims for their wonderful conduct so far in Israel which according to him,  is expected of them as they have always been. Gorap explained that his expectations would be to have a spiritually fulfilled pilgrimage anchored on prayers. He thanked the Nigeria Christian Pilgrim Commission for the effective leadership it has put in place to make this year’s pilgrimage a hitch-free exercise. The first batch of intending pilgrims from Plateau State departed  Abuja on 17 December and would complete their pilgrimage circle on 26th December when they are expected to return back to Nigeria. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
